pipeline_summary.name: multi_region_ecommerce_analytics
pipeline_summary.description: Multiregion ecommerce analytics pipeline performing ingestion, currency conversion, and aggregation.

components.name: Start Pipeline
components.description: Marks the entry point of the pipeline execution.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this is the first task.

components.name: Ingest Regional Sales Data
components.description: Extracts sales CSV files for each geographic region (US-East, US-West, EU, APAC).

components.name: Convert Regional Currency to USD
components.description: Converts sales amounts from regional currencies to USD using predefined exchange rates (EURUSD, JPYUSD; USD regions are noops).

upstream_policy.description: Executes after the corresponding ingest_regional_sales task for the same region.

components.name: Aggregate Global Revenue Report
components.description: Combines converted regional sales data into a unified global revenue CSV report for the execution date.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after all convert_currency tasks have completed successfully.

components.name: End Pipeline
components.description: Marks successful completion of the pipeline.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after the aggregate_global_revenue task completes successfully.

description.default: Multiregion ecommerce analytics pipeline performing ingestion, currency conversion, and aggregation.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

region.description: Geographic region to ingest sales data
Geographic region whose currency will be converted to USD

provide_context.description: Flag to enable XCom context access for aggregation

sources: USEast regional sales CSV files located at /data/us_east
USWest regional sales CSV files located at /data/us_west
EU regional sales CSV files located at /data/eu
APAC regional sales CSV files located at /data/apac
sinks: Global revenue report CSV written to /data/global_reports (filename includes execution date)
